{{coord|33.5013|-101.8844|type:edu_region:US-TX|display=title}}
'''All Saints [[Episcopal Church (United States)|Episcopal]] School''' is a private school in [[Lubbock, Texas]]. It was founded in 1957 as St. Christopher's School and was initially operated by St. Christopher's Episcopal Church.
In June 1975 the school became independent with its own [[board of trustees]] and changed its name to All Saints Episcopal School. It has 320 students and operates from pre-[[kindergarten]] to [[grade 9]].
They are currently building a [[high school]] financed by Happy State Bank and being built by Lee Lewis Construction Inc.

